## Room Overview

CyberChef is a browser-based "Swiss Army knife" for data manipulation, built by GCHQ. It's used constantly in SOC/DFIR work for decoding, extracting, and transforming data without writing custom scripts. CyberChef works on **recipes** — an ordered chain of operations applied to input data. This room covers the interface, the general workflow for approaching an unknown blob of data, and hands-on practice with common operations.

